cs.SD, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.MM

The paper proposes a novel fully convolutional network for multichannel speech enhancement that operates in the time domain. This suggests that the paper may belong to the Signal Processing (cs.SD) or Computation and Language (cs.CL) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper uses deep learning models, which are often associated with the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Sound (cs.SI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed methods on two multichannel SE tasks, which suggests that it may also belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
